sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderCell.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new HeaderCell. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeigth heigth} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100px)
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 106px)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getWest west} : sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderCellItem
    • {@link #getNorth north} : sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderCellItem
    • {@link #getEast east} : sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderCellItem
    • {@link #getSouth south} : sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderCellItem
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Status.helpDescription:
The status element holds information about a custom status that can be applied to nodes, lines, and groups of nodes.

You can create multiple custom statuses and assign them to your graph using the statuses aggregation of the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Graph} control.

Alternatively, you can use default statuses provided by the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementStatus} element.
sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Status.description:
The status element holds information about a custom status that can be applied to nodes, lines, and groups of nodes.

You can create multiple custom statuses and assign them to your graph using the statuses aggregation of the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Graph} control.

Alternatively, you can use default statuses provided by the {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementStatus} element.
sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Status.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Status. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getKey key} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getBorderColor borderColor} : string
    • {@link #getBackgroundColor backgroundColor} : string
    • {@link #getContentColor contentColor} : string
    • {@link #getHeaderContentColor headerContentColor} : string
    • {@link #getHoverBackgroundColor hoverBackgroundColor} : string
    • {@link #getHoverBorderColor hoverBorderColor} : string
    • {@link #getHoverContentColor hoverContentColor} : string
    • {@link #getSelectedBackgroundColor selectedBackgroundColor} : string
    • {@link #getSelectedBorderColor selectedBorderColor} : string
    • {@link #getSelectedContentColor selectedContentColor} : string
    • {@link #getLegendColor legendColor} : string
    • {@link #getUseFocusColorAsContentColor useFocusColorAsContentColor} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getBorderWidth borderWidth} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize
    • {@link #getBorderStyle borderStyle} : string
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Element#constructor sap.ui.core.Element} can be used as well.

discreteThresholds.helpDescription:
Specifies discrete thresholds for the status indicator. If discrete thresholds are set, the status indicator adjusts its appearance to the closest threshold value that is not greater than the actual percentage value of the status indicator. For example, if the following discrete thresholds are specified:
  • value = "20"
  • value = "60"
  • value = "100"
The status indicator displays the following percentage values:
  • 0 if the actual value is 15
  • 20 if the actual value is 20
  • 20 if the actual value is 55
  • 60 if the actual value is 60
  • 60 if the actual value is 79
  • 100 if the actual value is 100
Please note that these thresholds affect only the appearance of the status inicator, not its stored value.

sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Sta.helpDescription: The status indicator control displays a value between 0 and 100. A status indicator may consist of multiple groups that gradually display the value. The shapes in the first group are filled first, the shapes in the second group second, and so on. The value of the status indicator is distributed between the groups depending on their weight. The filling of the shapes in the groups can be proportional to the value of the status indicator or can be based on thresholds specified in the discreteThresholds aggregation.

The supported settings are:

    • {@link #getAriaLabel ariaLabel} : string
    • {@link #getSize size} : sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.SizeType (default: None)
    • {@link #getLabelPosition labelPosition} : sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.LabelPositionType (default: Left)
    • {@link #getShowLabel showLabel} : boolean (default: false)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getGroups groups} : sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.ShapeGroup[] (default)
    • {@link #getPropertyThresholds propertyThresholds} : sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.PropertyThreshold[]
    • {@link #getDiscreteThresholds discreteThresholds} : sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.DiscreteThreshold[]
    • {@link #getLabel label} : sap.m.Text
  • Associations
    • {@link #getAriaDescribedBy ariaDescribedBy} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)[]
    • {@link #getAriaLabelledBy ariaLabelledBy} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)[]

sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowLaneHead.helpDescription: This control gives you an overview of documents or items used in a process flow. The process flow is represented by donut chart sections that are colored according to the status of documents. This control can be used in two different ways. If you use it standalone, an event is triggered and can be caught to display the node map. If you use it with nodes or documents, it gives you an overview of the documents or items used in the process flow, which is represented by the donut chart sections.

drawData.helpDescription: This is an array of the following attributes for one element: 1. flowLine (string) - A connection definition where the line should be drawn. A string which defines a course of a flow line. A flow line is a connection between nodes in a process flow control. The string can contain the following characters: - "r" for right, - "t" for top, - "l" for left, - "b" for bottom. 2. targetNodeState (ProcessFlowNodeState) - A copy of the target node status. If the target node is created, the line is solid. If the target node is planned, the line is dashed. 3. displayState (ProcessFlowDisplayState) - Display state of the node. This property defines if the node is displayed regularly, highlighted, or dimmed in combination with a selected visual style of the control. 4. hasArrow (boolean) - Indicates if the line has an arrow on the right end.

sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnecti.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ProcessFlowConnection. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getDrawData drawData} : object[]
    • {@link #getZoomLevel zoomLevel} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowZoomLevel (default: Two)
    • {@link #getType type} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnectionType (default: Normal)
    • {@link #getState state} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnectionState (default: Regular)
  • Aggregations
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

  • Properties
    • {@link #getItemMinWidth itemMinWidth} : int
    • {@link #getResponsive responsive} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getDefaultViewIndex defaultViewIndex} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getShowSearchField showSearchField} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowViews showViews} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getExternal external} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getItemHeight itemHeight} : int
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getViews views} : sap.suite.ui.commons.RepeaterViewConfiguration[]
  • Associations
    • {@link #getExternalRepresentation externalRepresentation} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:search search} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:changeView changeView} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater#constructor sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard.description: This control allows you to store Note Taker card header and body text.
sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new NoteTakerCard. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeader header} : string
    • {@link #getBody body} : string
    • {@link #getTimestamp timestamp} : object (default: new Date())
    • {@link #getTags tags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getViewAllTrigger viewAllTrigger} : int (default: 1800)
    • {@link #getUid uid} : string
    • {@link #getIsFiltered isFiltered} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getThumbUp thumbUp} : boolean
    • {@link #getThumbDown thumbDown} : boolean
    • {@link #getAllTags allTags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getAttachmentFilename attachmentFilename} : string
    • {@link #getAttachmentUrl attachmentUrl} : string
  • Events
    • {@link #event:editNote editNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:deleteNote deleteNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentClick attachmentClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ForceDirectedLayout. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getOptimalDistanceConstant optimalDistanceConstant} : float (default: 0.2)
    • {@link #getMaxIterations maxIterations} : int (default: 200)
    • {@link #getMaxTime maxTime} : int (default: 2000)
    • {@link #getInitialTemperature initialTemperature} : float (default: 200)
    • {@link #getCoolDownStep coolDownStep} : float (default: 1)
    • {@link #getStaticNodes staticNodes} : string[] (default: [])
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm} can be used as well.

    • {@link #getStretchToCenter stretchToCenter} : boolean (default: false)

    • {@link #getCoordinates coordinates} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Coordinate[]
    • {@link #getActionButtons actionButtons} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ActionButton[]

    • {@link #event:hover hover} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

sap.suite.ui.commons.DateRangeScroller.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.34 Deprecated. Not Fiori.
The DateRangeScroller provides a method to scroll through a series of time periods, each of which is represented by a starting date and an ending date, known as the date range. The user may scroll to the previous or next date range. Several predefined ranges are supported such as day, week, work week, month, and year.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.GraphM.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new GraphMap. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: )
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: )
    • {@link #getDirectRenderNodeLimit directRenderNodeLimit} : int (default: 250)
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string (default: )
  • Associations
    • {@link #getGraph graph} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Graph)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:mapReady mapReady} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

fullAnimationDuration.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

fillingAngle.helpDescription:
Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear.

sap.suite.ui.commons.NumericTile.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new NumericTile. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getValue value} : string
    • {@link #getScale scale} : string
    • {@link #getUnit unit} : string
    • {@link #getValueColor valueColor} : sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTileValueColor
    • {@link #getIndicator indicator} : sap.suite.ui.commons.DeviationIndicator (default: None)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTile#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTile} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.UnifiedThingInspect.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new UnifiedThingInspector. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getName name} : string
    • {@link #getDescription description} : string
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getTransactionsVisible transactionsVisible} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getActionsVisible actionsVisible} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getDestroyPageOnBack destroyPageOnBack} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getConfigurationVisible configurationVisible} : boolean (default: true)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getFacets facets} : sap.suite.ui.commons.FacetOverview[]
    • {@link #getFacetContent facetContent} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getKpis kpis} : sap.suite.ui.commons.KpiTile[]
    • {@link #getTransactions transactions} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getActions actions} : sap.m.Button[]
    • {@link #getPages pages} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:backAction backAction} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:transactionsButtonPress transactionsButtonPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:actionsButtonPress actionsButtonPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:configurationButtonPress configurationButtonPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:navigate navigate} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:afterNavigate afterNavigate} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.SplitButton.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.34 Deprecated. Not Fiori.
The Split Button Control is a composite control that consists of a default-action Button and a Menu Button control. The default-action button control represents a simple push button. It is used for initiating actions, such as save or print. It can contain some text, an icon, or both; the order of the two can be configured. The action initiated by this button is considered to be the default action for the control, and it must be one of the selections defined in the Menu Button menu. The Menu Button control is a button that opens a menu upon user's click. MenuButton is a composition of the Menu control and the Button control and thus inheriting all features. When a menu item is selected by the user, MenuButton throws an event called itemSelected. The event transfers the itemId of the selected item. As an alternative, the button press event can be used which has a similar behavior.

DeprecatedInfo.description: Deprecated. Not Fiori.

sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNode.helpDescription: This control enables you to see documents (or other items) in respect to their statuses – positive, negative, neutral, planned, planned negative. In addition to the node title (which can be optionally a hyperlink) also two other text fields are provided and can be filled. The process flow nodes consider all styles depending on the status they are in. The user can update or change the content of the node. The content of the node can be also filtered according to updated data and specific parameters set. This means that also the node’s style is affected.

sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNode.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ProcessFlowNode. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getIsTitleClickable isTitleClickable} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getLaneId laneId} : string
    • {@link #getNodeId nodeId} : string
    • {@link #getState state} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNodeState (default: Neutral)
    • {@link #getType type} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNodeType (default: Single)
    • {@link #getChildren children} : any[]
    • {@link #getTitleAbbreviation titleAbbreviation} : string
    • {@link #getStateText stateText} : string
    • {@link #getTexts texts} : string[]
    • {@link #getHighlighted highlighted} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getFocused focused} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getTag tag} : object
    • {@link #getSelected selected} : boolean (default: false)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getZoomLevelOneContent zoomLevelOneContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getZoomLevelTwoContent zoomLevelTwoContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getZoomLevelThreeContent zoomLevelThreeContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getZoomLevelFourContent zoomLevelFourContent} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getAriaProperties ariaProperties} : sap.suite.ui.commons.AriaProperties
  • Associations
    • {@link #getParents parents} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNode)[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:titlePress titlePress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

fillingAngle.helpDescription:
Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear.

fullAnimationDuration.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Cus.description: Custom shape that is defined directly as SVG.
sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Cus.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new CustomShape. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getX x} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getY y} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getStrokeColor strokeColor} : sap.m.ValueCSSColor (default: Neutral)
    • {@link #getStrokeWidth strokeWidth} : float (default: 0.25)
    • {@link #getDefinition definition} : string
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getShapes shapes} : sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.SimpleShape[] (default)
    • {@link #getFillingOptions fillingOptions} : sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingOption[]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Shape#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Shape} can be used as well.

fillingAngle.helpDescription:
Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear.

fullAnimationDuration.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEd.helpDescription: Image editor displays an image and provides API and visual controls to edit it.
sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEd.description: Image editor displays an image and provides API and visual controls to edit it.
sap.suite.ui.commons.imageeditor.ImageEd.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ImageEditor. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getSrc src} : string (default: )
    • {@link #getMode mode} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ImageEditorMode (default: Default)
    • {@link #getKeepCropAspectRatio keepCropAspectRatio} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getKeepResizeAspectRatio keepResizeAspectRatio} : boolean (default: true)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:loaded loaded} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:error error} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:sizeChanged sizeChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:cropAreaChanged cropAreaChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:zoomChanged zoomChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:historyChanged historyChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTaker.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new NoteTaker. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getVisibleNotes visibleNotes} : int (default: 2)
    • {@link #getCardViewAllTrigger cardViewAllTrigger} : int (default: 1800)
    • {@link #getFilterCriteria filterCriteria} : object
    • {@link #getAttachmentUploadUrl attachmentUploadUrl} : string
    • {@link #getAttachmentName attachmentName} : string (default: attachment)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getCards cards} : sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:addCard addCard} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:deleteCard deleteCard} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:editCard editCard} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentSelect attachmentSelect} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentUploadComplete attachmentUploadComplete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentDelete attachmentDelete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentClick attachmentClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

scrollable.helpDescription:
By default, the control body is embedded into a scroll container of fixed size, so the user can put the control into a fixed size layout. When the control body (the graph) gets larger, the container cuts the overflowing parts of the graph and the cut parts can be displayed by scrolling the control body. When the control body fits into the container limits, obviously no scrolling is possible (and makes sense).

The scrolling feature can be turned off by setting this property value to false, so the width/height of the whole control will change as the flow graph gets smaller/larger. In this case the control body could not be scrolled, as the control body size matches the control container size.

fillingAngle.helpDescription:
Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear.

fullAnimationDuration.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.Rec.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Rectangle. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getX x} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getY y} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getRx rx} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getRy ry} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getHeight height} : int (default: 0)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.SimpleShape#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.SimpleShape} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerFeeder.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new NoteTakerFeeder. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getBody body} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getTags tags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getThumbUp thumbUp} : boolean
    • {@link #getThumbDown thumbDown} : boolean
    • {@link #getAttachmentUploadUrl attachmentUploadUrl} : string
    • {@link #getAttachmentName attachmentName} : string (default: attachment)
  • Aggregations
  • Events
    • {@link #event:addNote addNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentSelect attachmentSelect} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentUploadComplete attachmentUploadComplete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentDelete attachmentDelete} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:attachmentClick attachmentClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new LayeredLayout. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getNodeSpacing nodeSpacing} : float (default: 55)
    • {@link #getLineSpacingFactor lineSpacingFactor} : float (default: 0.25)
    • {@link #getNodePlacement nodePlacement} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.NodePlacement (default: BrandesKoepf)
    • {@link #getMergeEdges mergeEdges} : boolean (default: false)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm} can be used as well.

dateTime.helpDescription:
Date and time value of the timeline post. This value must be in one of the following formats:
  • A valid instance of the Date object.
  • An integer representing Unix time (also known as POSIX or Epoch time) in milliseconds.
  • A string with an integer representing Unix time in milliseconds.
  • A string that contains Date([number]), where [number] represents Unix time in milliseconds.
If this property has any other format, the timeline will try to parse it using Date.parse. It is not recommended to use this functionality, as different web browsers implement this function differently, which may lead to unpredictable behavior.

maxCharacters.helpDescription: The expand and collapse feature is set by default and uses 300 characters on mobile devices and 500 characters on desktop computers as limits. Based on these values, the text of the timeline post is collapsed once it reaches these character limits. In this case, only the specified number of characters is displayed. By clicking the More link, the entire text can be displayed. Clicking Less collapses the text. The application can set the value according to its needs.

sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineItem.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new TimelineItem. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getDateTime dateTime} : any
    • {@link #getFilterValue filterValue} : string
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : string
    • {@link #getIconTooltip iconTooltip} : string
    • {@link #getUseIconTooltip useIconTooltip} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getMaxCharacters maxCharacters} : int
    • {@link #getReplyCount replyCount} : int
    • {@link #getStatus status} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getText text} : string
    • {@link #getUserName userName} : string
    • {@link #getUserNameClickable userNameClickable} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getUserPicture userPicture} : sap.ui.core.URI
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getCustomAction customAction} : sap.ui.core.CustomData[]
    • {@link #getCustomReply customReply} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getEmbeddedControl embeddedControl} : sap.ui.core.Control (default)
    • {@link #getReplyList replyList} : sap.m.List
    • {@link #getSuggestionItems suggestionItems} : sap.m.StandardListItem[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:userNameClicked userNameClicked} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:replyPost replyPost} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:replyListOpen replyListOpen} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:customActionClicked customActionClicked} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:suggest suggest} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:suggestionItemSelected suggestionItemSelected} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

textHeight.helpDescription:
Height of the timeline posts. It can be set to either of the following types of values:
  • Automatic – If set to automatic, the optimal post height is calculated automatically to fit the timeline height specified by the height parameter. This option works only in horizontal timelines and only when the timeline height is defined. In vertical timelines, this setting is ignored.
  • Number – If set to a number, a corresponding number of text lines is displayed in every post.
  • Pixels – If set to a number followed by px, such as 50px, the closest number in lines is calculated and applied to the timeline posts, so that the post height corresponds to the specified number of pixels and the text lines are not cut off in the middle of a line.
  • Any other valid {@link sap.ui.core.CSSSize CSSSize} value that is inserted into the text wrapper without being changed.

enableModelFilter.helpDescription: Enables filtering directly on the binding level. If set to true, all filters are translated into the filters in the model binding. When the OData model is used, the filtering is performed on the backend side. This option is strongly recommended. If set to false, all entries from the model need to be fetched before they can be filtered on the frontend side. Please be aware that the growingThreshold property determines how many entries can be rendered. Timeline requests all entries from the model before it performs the filtering. Some models may have internal limits for the number of entries that can be used in bindings. Such limits can be set using {@link sap.ui.model.Model#setSizeLimit}.

sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline.helpDescription:
The timeline control shows entries (such as objects, events, or posts) in chronological order.
A common use case is to provide information about changes to an object, or events related to an object. These entries can be generated by the system (for example, value XY changed from A to B), or added manually.
There are two distinct variants of the timeline: basic and social. The basic timeline is read-only, while the social timeline offers a high level of interaction and collaboration, and is integrated within SAP Jam.

The timeline control shows entries (such as objects, events, or posts) in chronological order.
A common use case is to provide information about changes to an object, or events related to an object. These entries can be generated by the system (for example, value XY changed from A to B), or added manually.
There are two distinct variants of the timeline: basic and social. The basic timeline is read-only, while the social timeline offers a high level of interaction and collaboration, and is integrated within SAP Jam.
sap.suite.ui.commons.Timeline.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Timeline. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getAlignment alignment} : sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineAlignment (default: Right)
    • {@link #getAxisOrientation axisOrientation} : sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineAxisOrientation (default: Vertical)
    • {@link #getData data} : object
    • {@link #getEnableAllInFilterItem enableAllInFilterItem} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEnableBackendFilter enableBackendFilter} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEnableBusyIndicator enableBusyIndicator} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEnableDoubleSided enableDoubleSided} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEnableModelFilter enableModelFilter} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEnableScroll enableScroll} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEnableSocial enableSocial} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getFilterTitle filterTitle} : string
    • {@link #getForceGrowing forceGrowing} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getGroup group} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getGroupBy groupBy} : string
    • {@link #getGroupByType groupByType} : sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineGroupType (default: None)
    • {@link #getGrowing growing} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getGrowingThreshold growingThreshold} : int (default: 5)
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: )
    • {@link #getLazyLoading lazyLoading} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getNoDataText noDataText} : string
    • {@link #getScrollingFadeout scrollingFadeout} : sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineScrollingFadeout (default: None)
    • {@link #getShowFilterBar showFilterBar} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowHeaderBar showHeaderBar} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowIcons showIcons} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowItemFilter showItemFilter} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowSearch showSearch} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowSort showSort} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowSuggestion showSuggestion} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowTimeFilter showTimeFilter} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getSort sort} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getSortOldestFirst sortOldestFirst} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getTextHeight textHeight} : string (default: )
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineItem[] (default)
    • {@link #getCustomFilter customFilter} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getFilterList filterList} : sap.suite.ui.commons.TimelineFilterListItem[]
    • {@link #getSuggestionItems suggestionItems} : sap.m.StandardListItem[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:addPost addPost} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:customMessageClosed customMessageClosed} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:filterOpen filterOpen} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:filterSelectionChange filterSelectionChange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:grow grow} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:itemFiltering itemFiltering} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:select select} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:suggest suggest} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:suggestionItemSelected suggestionItemSelected} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.ChartContainer.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ChartContainer. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getShowPersonalization showPersonalization} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowFullScreen showFullScreen} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getFullScreen fullScreen} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowLegend showLegend} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string (default: )
    • {@link #getSelectorGroupLabel selectorGroupLabel} : string
    • {@link #getAutoAdjustHeight autoAdjustHeight} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowZoom showZoom} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowLegendButton showLegendButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowSelectionDetails showSelectionDetails} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getWrapLabels wrapLabels} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEnableScroll enableScroll} : boolean (default: true)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getDimensionSelectors dimensionSelectors} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ChartContainerContent[] (default)
    • {@link #getToolbar toolbar} : sap.m.OverflowToolbar
    • {@link #getCustomIcons customIcons} : sap.ui.core.Icon[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:personalizationPress personalizationPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:contentChange contentChange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:customZoomInPress customZoomInPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:customZoomOutPress customZoomOutPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.KpiTile.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new KpiTile. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getValue value} : string
    • {@link #getDescription description} : string
    • {@link #getDoubleFontSize doubleFontSize} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getValueUnit valueUnit} : string
    • {@link #getValueScale valueScale} : string
    • {@link #getValueStatus valueStatus} : sap.suite.ui.commons.ValueStatus (default: Neutral)
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.MicroProcessFlow.helpDescription:
The MicroProcessFlow control can be used to track the progress of a process.
It is best used for linear processes, such as document, order, and approval flows, and can be embedded in tiles, tables, and other containers.

To display more complex processes and workflows, use {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlow} instead.

sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderContainer.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.44 This control is deprecated in this library since 1.44 and moved to sap.m library that is also part of openUI5.
The container that provides a horizontal layout. It provides a horizontal scroll on the tablet and phone. On the desktop, it provides scroll left and scroll right buttons. This control supports keyboard navigation. You can use left and right arrow keys to navigate through the inner content. The Home key puts focus on the first control and the End key puts focus on the last control. Use Enter or Space to choose the control.

DeprecatedInfo.description: This control is deprecated in this library since 1.44 and moved to sap.m library that is also part of openUI5.

On the desktop, it provides scroll left and scroll right buttons. This control supports keyboard navigation. You can use left and right arrow keys to navigate through the inner content. The Home key puts focus on the first control and the End key puts focus on the last control. Use Enter or Space to choose the control.
sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderContainer.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new HeaderContainer. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getScrollStep scrollStep} : int (default: 300)
    • {@link #getScrollTime scrollTime} : int (default: 500)
    • {@link #getShowDividers showDividers} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getView view} : sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderContainerView (default: Horizontal)
    • {@link #getBackgroundDesign backgroundDesign} : sap.m.BackgroundDesign (default: Transparent)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getItems items} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)

    • {@link #getEnableZoom enableZoom} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEnableWheelZoom enableWheelZoom} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getBackgroundImage backgroundImage} : sap.ui.core.URI
    • {@link #getBackgroundColor backgroundColor} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.BackgroundColor (default: White)
    • {@link #getRenderType renderType} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.RenderType (default: Html)
    • {@link #getNoData noData} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getNoDataText noDataText} : string (default: )
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getLines lines} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Line[]
    • {@link #getNodes nodes} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Node[]
    • {@link #getGroups groups} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Group[]
    • {@link #getLegend legend} : sap.ui.core.Control
    • {@link #getLayoutAlgorithm layoutAlgorithm} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.layout.LayoutAlgorithm
    • {@link #getStatuses statuses} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Status[]
  • Associations
    • {@link #getAriaDescribedBy ariaDescribedBy} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)[]
    • {@link #getAriaLabelledBy ariaLabelledBy} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:graphReady graphReady} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:afterLayouting afterLayouting} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:beforeLayouting beforeLayouting} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:zoomChanged zoomChanged} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:failure failure} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:selectionChange selectionChange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:searchSuggest searchSuggest} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:search search} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.SvgBase#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.SvgBase} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.DateRangeSlider.description: The Date Range Slider provides the user with a Range Slider control that is optimized for use with Dates.
sap.suite.ui.commons.DateRangeSlider.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new DateRangeSlider. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 100%)
    • {@link #getEnabled enabled} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getEditable editable} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowBubbles showBubbles} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getSmallStepWidth smallStepWidth} : float
    • {@link #getTotalUnits totalUnits} : int
    • {@link #getStepLabels stepLabels} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getLabels labels} : string[]
    • {@link #getMin min} : object
    • {@link #getMax max} : object
    • {@link #getValue value} : object
    • {@link #getValue2 value2} : object
    • {@link #getPinGrip pinGrip} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getPinGrip2 pinGrip2} : boolean (default: false)
  • Events
    • {@link #event:change change} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:liveChange liveChange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

fullAnimationDuration.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

fillingAngle.helpDescription:
Defines the angle at which the shape is filled. This property overrides the fillingDirection property.
Accepted values include 0 through 360 degrees.
For example, if you set the filling angle to 45, the shape will be filled diagonally from the lower right part of the shape to its upper left part.
This property can be used only when {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.statusindicator.FillingType} is set to Linear.

sap.suite.ui.commons.FacetOverview.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new FacetOverview. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getQuantity quantity} : int (default: -1)
    • {@link #getWidth width} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: auto)
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: 10rem)
    • {@link #getRowSpan rowSpan} : int (default: 1)
    • {@link #getHeightType heightType} : sap.suite.ui.commons.FacetOverviewHeight (default: None)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.ui.core.Control
  • Events
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:heightChange heightChange} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

weight.helpDescription:
Weight of the group, relative to other groups in the status indicator. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between groups of shapes that it contains. For example, for three groups with weights 10, 10, and 20 (total weight 40), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 25% (10 out of 40), the first group of shapes (weight 10) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value is 5, the first group of shapes is 1/5-full. The second and the third groups are empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 25% but below 50%, the first group of shapes (weight 10) is filled, the second group (also weight 10) is partially filled, and the third group (weight 20) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 50% but below 100%, the first two groups of shapes (weight 10 each) are filled, but the third group (weight 20) is only partially filled.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all three groups of shapes are filled.
weight.description:
Weight of the group, relative to other groups in the status indicator. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between groups of shapes that it contains. For example, for three groups with weights 10, 10, and 20 (total weight 40), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 25% (10 out of 40), the first group of shapes (weight 10) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value is 5, the first group of shapes is 1/5-full. The second and the third groups are empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 25% but below 50%, the first group of shapes (weight 10) is filled, the second group (also weight 10) is partially filled, and the third group (weight 20) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 50% but below 100%, the first two groups of shapes (weight 10 each) are filled, but the third group (weight 20) is only partially filled.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all three groups of shapes are filled.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Elemen.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new ElementBase. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getDescription description} : string
    • {@link #getStatus status} : string (default: sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementStatus.Standard)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getAttributes attributes} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementAttribute[]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.SvgBase#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.SvgBase} can be used as well.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getMeasureOfUnit measureOfUnit} : string (default: )

    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getSubtitle subtitle} : string
    • {@link #getOrderBy orderBy} : string (default: )
    • {@link #getOpening opening} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getOpeningDebit openingDebit} : float (default: 0)

  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getDebit debit} : sap.suite.ui.commons.taccount.TAccountItem[]
    • {@link #getCredit credit} : sap.suite.ui.commons.taccount.TAccountItem[]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Group.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Group. Grouping is not supported for custom layouting. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeaderCheckBoxState headerCheckBoxState} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.HeaderCheckboxState (default: Hidden)
    • {@link #getKey key} : string
    • {@link #getCollapsed collapsed} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : string
    • {@link #getMinWidth minWidth} : float (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getParentGroupKey parentGroupKey} : string
  • Aggregations
  • Events
    • {@link #event:headerCheckBoxPress headerCheckBoxPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:collapseExpand collapseExpand} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:showDetail showDetail} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase} can be used as well.

fullAnimationDuration.helpDescription:
Deprecated! Since 1.54.1 All animations are now limited to 250 ms.
Specifies the duration, in milliseconds, of the animation that would fill an empty shape to the full. The actual time it takes to change the shape's filling is proportional to the difference between the initial and the target status indicator's value. For example, a change from 20 percent to 70 percent takes only half of the time specified in the fullAnimationDuration property. If this property is set to 0, changes are applied instantly without any animation.

weight.helpDescription:
Weight of the fillable shape, relative to other fillable shapes included in this custom shape. This property allows you to distribute the status indicator's value between distinct SVG shapes included in the custom shape. For example, for four SVG shapes with weights 1, 2, 3, and 4 (total weight 10), the status indicator's value is distributed in the following way:
  • If the status indicator's value is below 10% (1 out of 10), the first SVG shape (weight 1) is partially filled, depending on the percentage value. For example, if the percentage value of the status indicator is 5, the first SVG shape appears half-full. The rest of the SVG shapes appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 10% but below 30%, the first SVG shape (weight 1) is filled, and the second shape (weight 2) is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value. The rest of the SVG shapes in this custom shape appear empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 30% but below 60%, the first two SVG shapes (weight 1 and 2) are filled, and the third SVG shape (weight 3) is filled only partially. The fourth SVG shape (weight 4) appears empty.
  • If the status indicator's value is at least 60% but below 100%, the first three SVG shapes (weight 1, 2, and 3) are filled, but the fourth SVG shape is filled only partially, depending on the percentage value.
  • If the status indicator's value is 100, all four SVG shapes appear filled.

sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.Node.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new Node. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeaderCheckBoxState headerCheckBoxState} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.HeaderCheckboxState (default: Hidden)
    • {@link #getCollapsed collapsed} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getSelected selected} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getGroup group} : string
    • {@link #getKey key} : string
    • {@link #getShape shape} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.NodeShape (default: Circle)
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : string
    • {@link #getStatusIcon statusIcon} : string
    • {@link #getWidth width} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getHeight height} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getMaxWidth maxWidth} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getX x} : float (default: 0)
    • {@link #getY y} : float (default: 0)
    • {@link #getShowExpandButton showExpandButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowActionLinksButton showActionLinksButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowDetailButton showDetailButton} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getTitleLineSize titleLineSize} : int (default: 1)
    • {@link #getDescriptionLineSize descriptionLineSize} : int (default: -1)
    • {@link #getIconSize iconSize} : int (default: undefined)
    • {@link #getCoreNodeSize coreNodeSize} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getVisible visible} : boolean (default: true)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getActionLinks actionLinks} : sap.ui.core.Control[]
    • {@link #getActionButtons actionButtons} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ActionButton[]
    • {@link #getImage image} : sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.NodeImage
    • {@link #getContent content} : sap.ui.core.Control
  • Events
    • {@link #event:headerCheckBoxPress headerCheckBoxPress} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:hover hover} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:collapseExpand collapseExpand} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase#constructor sap.suite.ui.commons.networkgraph.ElementBase} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilder.helpDescription:
Calculation Builder allows you to perform arithmetic calculations on constants and variables using standard arithmetic operators as well as most common logical operators and functions.
You can customize the sets of variables and functions that are visible in the calculation builder and introduce your own custom functions, as needed.
Arithmetic expressions can be entered using a touch-friendly visual editor or a textual editor that provides autocomplete suggestions for variables and checks the expression syntax as you type.
sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilder.description:
Calculation Builder allows you to perform arithmetic calculations on constants and variables using standard arithmetic operators as well as most common logical operators and functions.
You can customize the sets of variables and functions that are visible in the calculation builder and introduce your own custom functions, as needed.
Arithmetic expressions can be entered using a touch-friendly visual editor or a textual editor that provides autocomplete suggestions for variables and checks the expression syntax as you type.
sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilder.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new calculation builder. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getExpression expression} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getShowToolbar showToolbar} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getWrapItemsInExpression wrapItemsInExpression} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getLayoutType layoutType} : string (default: Default)
    • {@link #getShowInputToolbar showInputToolbar} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getReadOnly readOnly} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getAllowComparisonOperators allowComparisonOperators} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getAllowLogicalOperators allowLogicalOperators} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getAllowSuggestions allowSuggestions} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getAllowStringConstants allowStringConstants} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getValidationMode validationMode} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderValidationMode (default: LiveChange)
    • {@link #getDisabledDefaultTokens disabledDefaultTokens} : string (default: )
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getItems items} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderItem[] (default)
    • {@link #getVariables variables} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderVariable[]
    • {@link #getFunctions functions} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderFunction[]
    • {@link #getOperators operators} : sap.ui.core.Item[]
    • {@link #getGroups groups} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderGroup[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:validateFunction validateFunction} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:change change} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:afterValidation afterValidation} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.

sap.suite.ui.commons.CalculationBuilderG.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new calculation builder variable group. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getKey key} : string
    • {@link #getTitle title} : string
    • {@link #getDescription description} : string
    • {@link #getIcon icon} : string
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getCustomView customView} : sap.ui.core.Control
  • Events
    • {@link #event:setSelection setSelection} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
